            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> For a zero-byte file this matters (`'' != '\\n'`), causing the bug. ...\n>\n> 1\\. Lua-side empty-file special case \n\nDo we just need to look at the 'fixeol' + 'eol' options? Item 1 is not a \"one-way door\"; a cheap, isolated fix is worthwhile to avoid rushing a more-expensive approach.\n\n> 2\\. Core-side trust hashing:\n\nDo we actually need that or do we just need an interface (or a documented \"recipe\") to \"get the actual buffer contents which would be written\")? Reminds me of:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34272\n",
