            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think we're open to any approach, just need a design proposal. Or maybe the ideas in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34272 are already there? \n\nFor this particular case, it sounds to me like we might need either:\n\n- a recipe to call `nvim_buf_get_text()` with the \"right arguments\" to get the \"actual buffer contents\"\n- or, introduce a `opts.foo` flag to `nvim_buf_get_text()` which gets the \"actual buffer contents\"",
